    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "FEATURE REQUEST:\r\nNew flag for the substitute command (:substitute / :s) to\r\nperform search and replace while keeping the case.\r\n\r\n\r\nHello,\r\n\r\nin Vim/NeoVim/MacVim/gVim there is currently no built-in solution\r\nto run search-and-replace in a way that the replacement text\r\nhas the same lower and upper case letters as the replaced text.\r\n\r\nWe suggest to add a new flag [k] that enables this behaviour.\r\n\r\nk == keep\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE:\r\n-------------\r\nfoo\r\nFoo\r\nFOO\r\n-------------\r\n:%s/foo/bar/k\r\n-------------\r\nbar\r\nBar\r\nBAR\r\n-------------\r\n\r\nI guess the k flag would implicitly also activate the i flag.\r\n\r\nAdditionally it could also be activated globally by extending the\r\noptions \"ignorecase\" and \"smartcase\" with a new setting e.g. \"keepcase\".\r\n\r\nThere is a plug-in called abolish.vim by Tim Pope that provides\r\nthis feature, but we have the opinion that it could be built-in.\r\nhttps://github.com/tpope/vim-abolish\r\n\r\nEven the \"enemy\" has it built-in.\r\nhttp://ergoemacs.org/emacs/emacs_find_replace.html\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks for thinking about it.\r\n\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\nInternational Vim User Group on Telegram\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
