            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I agree this would be an awesome feature, and found this issue when searching for if this feature existed.\n\nThere are plugins like: [tpopes's vim-abolish - subsititution section](https://github.com/tpope/vim-abolish#substitution) which will probably help give light on the problem/solution space (althought it does have other additional features that I am **not** punting, although a separate feature for snake/camel/pascal etc transforms is probably also a universal problem that would benefit the community)\n\n[text-case.nvim - bulk-smart-replacement](https://github.com/johmsalas/text-case.nvim#bulk-smart-replacement) does it although it's a bit rough, it works. They dont do the awesome live preview like neovim does, and this plugin by default applies to the whole buffer instead of the current line, you have to visual select a line to make it more like the default.  The main problem is since it has bespoke behavior, one can't use it with `:cdo`. But a great plugin for those desiring the feature for now.\n\nA native solution would be far superior and I think very beneficial to the community.\n\nI like the proposed `k` for keep, its short, its on the home room, will be easy to use and remember.\n\n",
